radiographic_examinations.findings: There are trace bilateral pleural effusions with associated bibasilar atelectasis. There is no mediastinal or axillary adenopathy. There is a 0.5 cm hypoattenuating lesion in the right kidney, likely represents a cyst. Small fat-containing right inguinal hernia.
